examples.en: He is skilled at cooking.
She is skilled at negotiation.
Nursing is a highly skilled job.
She's skilled in the art of conversation.
The department was reinforced with skilled personnel.
Carpentry is a skilled trade.
Bricklaying is very skilled work.
We need another highly skilled player to stave off defeat for our team.
A skilled surgeon has many years of training and experience.
The company is fortunate to have such highly skilled workers.
She's very skilled at dealing with the public.
nly the most skilled gymnasts make an Olympic team.
The statue took on life in the sculptor's skilled hands.
Media people need to be good talkers and skilled negotiators.
Skilled craftsmen carved the enormous mantel.
Skilled negotiators helped defuse the crisis.
There is a shortage of skilled labor in this field.
Employers hire skilled people on fixed-term contracts.
Skilled stalkers are shooting up to a dozen hinds a day.
Skilled craftsmen, such as carpenters, are in great demand.
Unskilled workers of today need to upgrade themselves to become the skilled workers of tomorrow.
He is a skilled forger who hoaxed the art world into believing that the paintings were long-lost Vermeers.
The kangaroo's forearms seem undeveloped but the powerful five-fingered hands are skilled at feinting and clouting.
They encountered an indigenous people who were experienced cultivators of the soil as well as highly skilled craftsmen.
